other_tests.findings: High-normal LH response (from 4.5 IU/L at T0 to 35.9 IU/L at T60) and mild FSH over-reaction (from 6.6 IU/L at T0 to 19.6 IU/L at T60).
Small uterus (45 x 320 mm) and small ovaries with few follicles; right ovary at 20 x 11 mm with follicles, left ovary atrophic without follicles.
KISS1R expression observed in epithelial cells but no staining when the first antibody was omitted.
Low estradiol level (11.8 pg/mL), inappropriately normal gonadotropin levels, undetectable inhibin B, and low AMH level (1.18 ng/mL).
Induced an LH surge, with LH levels reaching a mean of 29.00 IU/L on day 23.
other_tests.changes_over_time: The gonadotropin deficiency indicated was only partial over time despite initial KISS1R inactivation.
